Noted for day 27: 


Wait commands

It helps us with synchronization problem  -

Default - Thread.sleep(); method - it has disadvantages  - 
1)if time is not sufficient the it will throw exception
2)it will wait for maximum time out and it can effect your performance script
3)Multiple times

Wait commands  -- 
1)implicit wait -- driver.manage().timeout().implicitlyWait(duration);
write it after driver instance - it is applicable for all the code.

Adv 1: once it finds the element and it will not wait for max time out.
disadv: it max time out is done - it will throw an exception

2)explicit wait/fluent wait.
1:declare and use it - it is specifi to webpage

WebDriverWait mywait = new WebDriverWait(driver,Duration.ofSeconds(10));//declaration
conditions:
ADV: it is conditional based - will work more effectively
2:finding element is inclusive (for some condition)
3:it will wait for the condition to be true then consider the time
4:we need to write multiple statement for multiple elements 


1:alertsPresent();
2:elementSelectionStateToBe();
3:elementToBeClicable();
4:elementToBeSelected();
5:frameToBeAvailableAndSwitchToit();
6:invisibilityOfTheElementLocated();
7:invisibilityOfElementWithText();
8:presenceOfAllElementsLocatedBy();
9:presenceOfElementLocated();
10:textToBePresentInElement();
11:textToBePresentInElementLocated();
12:textToBePresentInElementValue();
13:titles();
14:VisibilityOfAllElements();
15:VisibilityOfAllElementsLocatedBy();
16:VisibilityOfAllElementsLocated();



